te dwarfs, neutron stars, and possibly black\nholes. For the case of young stars, conical winds and axial jets may appear in\ndifferent cases, including Class I young stars, classical T Tauri stars, and\nEXors. In EXors periods of enhanced accretion may lead to the formation of\nconical winds which correspond to the outflows observed from these stars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 27 Jan 2009 15:07:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-01-28"}
